Hello there. Cache reuse helps old hardware because the decode loop only adds the newest token work instead of repeating the full attention setup. The benefit must still fit inside the DOS memory budget. A cache matters for text generation because context is reused one token at a time. The model still attends to earlier tokens, but the runtime can store the key and value vectors that do not change.

