prompt: Why run a language model in DOS?
Why run a language model in DOS? Phase-vector checks compare the DOS fixed-point path with the host reference before the checkpoint is trusted. The scale must be chosen carefully so values keep useful precision without overflowing. Every scale and clamp is part of the correctness contract. How does the DOS runtime avoid depending on an FPU? Fixed-point inference stores weights as scaled integers and computes logits with predictable integer arithmetic.

